  "note": "Canonical decision index (D1–D36 → ADR-0001..0036). D1–D4 are the foundational conventions; D21 is the stack ADR (stack = agentic-delivery-pipeline, this repo's active profile); D22 (operator-approved amendment) sanctions deterministic helper tools the spine may shell out to; D23 adds the second stack ADR (stack = typescript) — the M12 Part-2 agnosticism proof, a sibling profile, not the active one. D24–D27 (CR-002, deterministic-machine) EXTEND D22: D24 schema-registry + structured-output (new frozen class), D25 io-manifest + resolver (new frozen class), D26 deterministic spine (Tier-1 emitters + verdict/route/seq/id/coverage compute), D27 the three open-decision resolutions (output grade · Tier-1 retirement · CR batching). D28 (CR-007, operator-approved) branch-per-workstream model — branch isolation + auto-reconcile + enforce-non-master + new-stream dispatch local-only. D29 (CR-008, operator-approved) Amendment-1 to D28 — brief.md branch: authoritative binding (R-MW-5) + Option-B auto-checkout + new HALT classes (wrong-branch, no-registration). D30 (CR-009, operator-approved) rename launcher command /self-host → /evolve, clean (no alias) — surface-rename only, self-host concept noun unchanged. D31 (CR-010, operator-approved) reranker ledger hygiene — prune complete+accepted+merged-wave records at STEP 0.1 (sentinel-on-master = merged), collapse-with-git-trail, preserve live records (D20: ledger is informational, not source of truth). D32 (CR-011, operator-approved) controller zero-write guarantee — controller-direct writes permitted only for mechanical deterministic ops (git, spine tool shell-outs, lock/index updates, scratch→promotion); rule prose, ADR bodies, CR docs route through step-runner clean-room (R-CW-1). D33 (CR-012, operator-approved) corrects D32 — splits R-CW-1 into three precise requirements: R-CW-1 (controller zero-write guarantee), R-CW-2 (orchestrator loop-control-only), R-CW-3 (step-runner authors+verifies). D32 marked superseded_by ADR-0033; D32 body frozen/untouched. D34 (CR-013, operator-approved) corrects D33 — kills controller/orchestrator conflation (D33 wrote \"Controller (orchestrator)\" equating two distinct entities; placed mechanical writes under Controller — wrong). D34 establishes three-tier write surfaces: Controller = zero writes (escalation gate + break-glass only); Orchestrator = loop control + permitted mechanical writes (git ops, spine shell-outs, lock/index re-sign, scratch→promotion); Step-runner = authors all artifact content + verifier = separate spawn. D33 marked superseded_by ADR-0034; D33 body frozen/untouched. D35 (CR-014, operator-approved) corrects D34 — kills /evolve-name leak in shared spine (.claude/agents/adp-orchestrator.md is invoked by BOTH /evolve AND /deliver; D34 hard-coded \"controller = /evolve session\" in R-CW-1, naming one command as canonical in a shared file). D35 rewrites R-CW-1 command-agnostic: controller = the Claude Code session that invokes an ADP launcher — /evolve OR /deliver, neither canonical. Also adds R-CW coverage to prompts/_orchestrator.generic.md (the /deliver loop body had none). D34 marked superseded_by ADR-0035; D34 body frozen/untouched. D36 (CR-015, operator-approved) introduces `audit` as the third brownfield delivery class — read-only lens-based assessment. Operator defines named lenses (check sets with pass/fail criteria); system audits existing code; produces `.audit/report.md` (human) + `.audit/audit-report.json` (machine); optional promote-to-initiative path emits `.aprd/00-raw-request.md`. Three net-new roles (LENS-DEFINE, AUDIT-RUN, AUDIT-REPORT) + two overlays (CLASSIFIER, BASELINE-MAP) deferred to subsequent builds. The index lives HERE as JSON, never as a markdown header (canonical fixture layout).",
